<section xml:id="C4.S21">
<title>Identities</title>          
<subsection xml:id="C4.S21.SS1">
<title>Addition Formulas</title>          
<para xml:id="C4.S21.SS1.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="1" xml:id="C4.S21.SS1.p1.s1">
 <Math equation-number="4.21.1" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S21.E1">\sin u\pm\cos u=\sqrt{2}\sin\left(u\pm\tfrac{1}{4}\pi\right)=\pm\sqrt{2}\cos \left(u\mp\tfrac{1}{4}\pi\right)</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="2" xml:id="C4.S21.SS1.p1.s2">
<Math equation-number="4.21.2" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S21.E2">\sin\left(u\pm v\right)=\sin u\cos v\pm\cos u\sin v,</Math> , <Math equation-number="4.21.3" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S21.E3">\cos\left(u\pm v\right)=\cos u\cos v\mp\sin u\sin v,</Math> , <Math equation-number="4.21.4" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S21.E4">\tan\left(u\pm v\right)=\frac{\tan u\pm\tan v}{1\mp\tan u\tan v},</Math> , <Math equation-number="4.21.5" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S21.E5">\cot\left(u\pm v\right)=\frac{\pm\cot u\cot v-1}{\cot u\pm\cot v}</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="3" sentence-num-in-section="3" xml:id="C4.S21.SS1.p1.s3">
<Math equation-number="4.21.6" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S21.E6">\sin u+\sin v=2\sin\left(\frac{u+v}{2}\right)\cos\left(\frac{u-v}{2}\right),</Math> , <Math equation-number="4.21.7" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S21.E7">\sin u-\sin v=2\cos\left(\frac{u+v}{2}\right)\sin\left(\frac{u-v}{2}\right),</Math> , <Math equation-number="4.21.8" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S21.E8">\cos u+\cos v=2\cos\left(\frac{u+v}{2}\right)\cos\left(\frac{u-v}{2}\right),</Math> , <Math equation-number="4.21.9" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S21.E9">\cos u-\cos v=-2\sin\left(\frac{u+v}{2}\right)\sin\left(\frac{u-v}{2}\right)</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="4" sentence-num-in-section="4" xml:id="C4.S21.SS1.p1.s4">
<Math equation-number="4.21.10" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S21.E10">\tan u\pm\tan v=\frac{\sin\left(u\pm v\right)}{\cos u\cos v},</Math> , <Math equation-number="4.21.11" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S21.E11">\cot u\pm\cot v=\frac{\sin\left(v\pm u\right)}{\sin u\sin v}</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
</subsection>
 
<subsection xml:id="C4.S21.SS2">
<title>Squares and Products</title>          
<para xml:id="C4.S21.SS2.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="5" xml:id="C4.S21.SS2.p1.s1">
 <Math equation-number="4.21.12" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S21.E12">{\sin^{2}}z+{\cos^{2}}z=1,</Math> <Math equation-number="4.21.13" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S21.E13">{\sec^{2}}z=1+{\tan^{2}}z,</Math> <Math equation-number="4.21.14" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S21.E14">{\csc^{2}}z=1+{\cot^{2}}z.</Math>
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="6" xml:id="C4.S21.SS2.p1.s2">
 <Math equation-number="4.21.15" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S21.E15">2\sin u\sin v=\cos\left(u-v\right)-\cos\left(u+v\right),</Math> <Math equation-number="4.21.16" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S21.E16">2\cos u\cos v=\cos\left(u-v\right)+\cos\left(u+v\right),</Math> <Math equation-number="4.21.17" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S21.E17">2\sin u\cos v=\sin\left(u-v\right)+\sin\left(u+v\right)</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="3" sentence-num-in-section="7" xml:id="C4.S21.SS2.p1.s3">
<Math equation-number="4.21.18" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S21.E18">{\sin^{2}}u-{\sin^{2}}v=\sin\left(u+v\right)\sin\left(u-v\right),</Math> , <Math equation-number="4.21.19" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S21.E19">{\cos^{2}}u-{\cos^{2}}v=-\sin\left(u+v\right)\sin\left(u-v\right),</Math> , <Math equation-number="4.21.20" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S21.E20">{\cos^{2}}u-{\sin^{2}}v=\cos\left(u+v\right)\cos\left(u-v\right)</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
</subsection>
 
<subsection xml:id="C4.S21.SS3">
<title>Multiples of the Argument</title>          
<para xml:id="C4.S21.SS3.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="8" xml:id="C4.S21.SS3.p1.s1">
 <Math equation-number="4.21.21" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S21.E21">\sin\frac{z}{2}=\pm\left(\frac{1-\cos z}{2}\right)^{1/2},</Math> <Math equation-number="4.21.22" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S21.E22">\cos\frac{z}{2}=\pm\left(\frac{1+\cos z}{2}\right)^{1/2},</Math> <Math equation-number="4.21.23" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S21.E23">\tan\frac{z}{2}=\pm\left(\frac{1-\cos z}{1+\cos z}\right)^{1/2}=\frac{1-\cos z }{\sin z}=\frac{\sin z}{1+\cos z}</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="9" xml:id="C4.S21.SS3.p1.s2">
In (4.21.21)–(4.21.23)Table 4.16.1 and analytic continuation will assist in resolving sign ambiguities.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="3" sentence-num-in-section="10" xml:id="C4.S21.SS3.p1.s3">
<Math equation-number="4.21.24" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S21.E24">\sin\left(-z\right)=-\sin z,</Math> , <Math equation-number="4.21.25" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S21.E25">\cos\left(-z\right)=\cos z,</Math> , <Math equation-number="4.21.26" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S21.E26">\tan\left(-z\right)=-\tan z</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="4" sentence-num-in-section="11" xml:id="C4.S21.SS3.p1.s4">
<Math equation-number="4.21.27" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S21.E27">\sin\left(2z\right)=2\sin z\cos z=\frac{2\tan z}{1+{\tan^{2}}z},</Math> <Math equation-number="4.21.28" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S21.E28">\cos\left(2z\right)=2{\cos^{2}}z-1=1-2{\sin^{2}}z={\cos^{2}}z-{\sin^{2}}z= \frac{1-{\tan^{2}}z}{1+{\tan^{2}}z},</Math> <Math equation-number="4.21.29" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S21.E29">\tan\left(2z\right)=\frac{2\tan z}{1-{\tan^{2}}z}=\frac{2\cot z}{{\cot^{2}}z-1 }=\frac{2}{\cot z-\tan z}</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="5" sentence-num-in-section="12" xml:id="C4.S21.SS3.p1.s5">
<Math equation-number="4.21.30" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S21.E30">\sin\left(3z\right)=3\sin z-4{\sin^{3}}z,</Math> , <Math equation-number="4.21.31" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S21.E31">\cos\left(3z\right)=-3\cos z+4{\cos^{3}}z,</Math> , <Math equation-number="4.21.32" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S21.E32">\sin\left(4z\right)=8{\cos^{3}}z\sin z-4\cos z\sin z,</Math> , <Math equation-number="4.21.33" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S21.E33">\cos\left(4z\right)=8{\cos^{4}}z-8{\cos^{2}}z+1</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
<paragraph xml:id="C4.S21.Px1">
<title>De Moivre’s Theorem</title>    
<para xml:id="C4.S21.Px1.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="13" xml:id="C4.S21.Px1.p1.s1">
When <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C4.S21.Px1.p1.m1">n\in\mathbb{Z}</Math> <Math equation-number="4.21.34" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S21.E34">\cos\left(nz\right)+i\sin\left(nz\right)=(\cos z+i\sin z)^{n}</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="14" xml:id="C4.S21.Px1.p1.s2">
This result is also valid when <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C4.S21.Px1.p1.m2">n</Math> is fractional or complex, provided that <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C4.S21.Px1.p1.m3">-\pi\leq\Re z\leq\pi</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="3" sentence-num-in-section="15" xml:id="C4.S21.Px1.p1.s3">
<Math equation-number="4.21.35" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S21.E35">\sin\left(nz\right)=2^{n-1}\prod_{k=0}^{n-1}\sin\left(z+\frac{k\pi}{n}\right), if n=1,2,3,\dots</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
<para xml:id="C4.S21.Px1.p2">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="16" xml:id="C4.S21.Px1.p2.s1">
If <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C4.S21.Px1.p2.m1">t=\tan\left(\frac{1}{2}z\right)</Math> , then <Math equation-number="4.21.36" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S21.E36">\sin z=\frac{2t}{1+t^{2}},\cos z=\frac{1-t^{2}}{1+t^{2}},\mathrm{d}z=\frac{2}{1+t^{2}}\mathrm{d}t</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
</paragraph>
 
</subsection>
 
<subsection xml:id="C4.S21.SS4">
<title>Real and Imaginary Parts; Moduli</title>         
  
<para xml:id="C4.S21.SS4.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="17" xml:id="C4.S21.SS4.p1.s1">
With <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C4.S21.SS4.p1.m1">z=x+iy</Math> <Math equation-number="4.21.37" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S21.E37">\sin z=\sin x\cosh y+\mathrm{i}\cos x\sinh y,</Math> <Math equation-number="4.21.38" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S21.E38">\cos z=\cos x\cosh y-\mathrm{i}\sin x\sinh y,</Math> <Math equation-number="4.21.39" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S21.E39">\tan z=\frac{\sin\left(2x\right)+\mathrm{i}\sinh\left(2y\right)}{\cos\left(2x \right)+\cosh\left(2y\right)},</Math> <Math equation-number="4.21.40" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S21.E40">\cot z=\frac{\sin\left(2x\right)-\mathrm{i}\sinh\left(2y\right)}{\cosh\left(2y \right)-\cos\left(2x\right)}</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="18" xml:id="C4.S21.SS4.p1.s2">
<Math equation-number="4.21.41" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S21.E41">|\sin z|=({\sin^{2}}x+{\sinh^{2}}y)^{1/2}=\left(\tfrac{1}{2}\left(\cosh\left(2 y\right)-\cos\left(2x\right)\right)\right)^{1/2},</Math> <Math equation-number="4.21.42" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S21.E42">|\cos z|=({\cos^{2}}x+{\sinh^{2}}y)^{1/2}=\left(\tfrac{1}{2}(\cosh\left(2y \right)+\cos\left(2x\right))\right)^{1/2},</Math> <Math equation-number="4.21.43" mode="display" xml:id="C4.S21.E43">|\tan z|=\left(\frac{\cosh\left(2y\right)-\cos\left(2x\right)}{\cosh\left(2y \right)+\cos\left(2x\right)}\right)^{1/2}</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>

 
</subsection>
 
</section>
